21/// A sandboxir::User with operands, opcode and linked with previous/next
22/// instructions in an instruction list.
23class Instruction : public User {
24public:
25 enum class Opcode {
26#define OP(OPC) OPC,
27#define OPCODES(...) __VA_ARGS__
28#define DEF_INSTR(ID, OPC, CLASS) OPC
29#include "llvm/SandboxIR/Values.def"
30 };
31
32protected:
33 Instruction(ClassID ID, Opcode Opc, llvm::Instruction *I,
34 sandboxir::Context &SBCtx)
35 : User(ID, I, SBCtx), Opc(Opc) {}

100 // Note that these functions below are calling into llvm::Instruction.
101 // A sandbox IR instruction could introduce a new opcode that could change the
102 // behavior of one of these functions. It is better that these functions are
103 // only added as needed and new sandbox IR instructions must explicitly check
104 // if any of these functions could have a different behavior.
105

341
342 /// We consider \p I as a Memory Dependency Candidate instruction if it
343 /// reads/write memory or if it has side-effects. This is used by the
344 /// dependency graph.
345 bool isMemDepCandidate() const {
346 auto *I = cast<llvm::Instruction>(Val);
347 return I->mayReadOrWriteMemory() &&
348 (!isa<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(I) ||
349 (cast<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(I)->getIntrinsicID() !=
350 Intrinsic::sideeffect &&
351 cast<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(I)->getIntrinsicID() !=
352 Intrinsic::pseudoprobe));
353 }

360/// Instructions that contain a single LLVM Instruction can inherit from this.
361template <typename LLVMT> class SingleLLVMInstructionImpl : public Instruction {
362 SingleLLVMInstructionImpl(ClassID ID, Opcode Opc, llvm::Instruction *I,
363 sandboxir::Context &SBCtx)
364 : Instruction(ID, Opc, I, SBCtx) {}
365
366 // All instructions are friends with this so they can call the constructor.
367#define DEF_INSTR(ID, OPC, CLASS) friend class CLASS;
368#include "llvm/SandboxIR/Values.def"
369 friend class UnaryInstruction;
370 friend class CallBase;
371 friend class FuncletPadInst;
372 friend class CmpInst;
373
374 Use getOperandUseInternal(unsigned OpIdx, bool Verify) const final {
375 return getOperandUseDefault(OpIdx, Verify);
376 }
377 SmallVector<llvm::Instruction *, 1> getLLVMInstrs() const final {
378 return {cast<llvm::Instruction>(Val)};
379 }
380
381public:
382 unsigned getUseOperandNo(const Use &Use) const final {
383 return getUseOperandNoDefault(Use);
384 }
385 unsigned getNumOfIRInstrs() const final { return 1u; }
386#ifndef NDEBUG
387 void verify() const final { assert(isa<LLVMT>(Val) && "Expected LLVMT!"); }
388 void dumpOS(raw_ostream &OS) const override {
389 dumpCommonPrefix(OS);
390 dumpCommonSuffix(OS);
391 }
392#endif
393};

395class FenceInst : public SingleLLVMInstructionImpl<llvm::FenceInst> {
396 FenceInst(llvm::FenceInst *FI, Context &Ctx)

398 friend Context; // For constructor;
399
400public:
401 static FenceInst *create(AtomicOrdering Ordering, BBIterator WhereIt,
402 BasicBlock *WhereBB, Context &Ctx,
403 SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System);
404 /// Returns the ordering constraint of this fence instruction.
405 AtomicOrdering getOrdering() const {
406 return cast<llvm::FenceInst>(Val)->getOrdering();
407 }
408 /// Sets the ordering constraint of this fence instruction. May only be
409 /// Acquire, Release, AcquireRelease, or SequentiallyConsistent.
410 void setOrdering(AtomicOrdering Ordering);
411 /// Returns the synchronization scope ID of this fence instruction.
412 SyncScope::ID getSyncScopeID() const {
413 return cast<llvm::FenceInst>(Val)->getSyncScopeID();
414 }
415 /// Sets the synchronization scope ID of this fence instruction.
416 void setSyncScopeID(SyncScope::ID SSID);

418 return From->getSubclassID() == ClassID::Fence;
419 }

668 /// Return true if this shuffle mask chooses elements from its source vectors
669 /// without lane crossings. A shuffle using this mask would be

675 /// (a length-changing shuffle can never be equivalent to a vector select).

733 return cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Val)->isZeroEltSplat();

736 /// Return true if this shuffle mask is a transpose mask.
737 /// Transpose vector masks transpose a 2xn matrix. They read corresponding
738 /// even- or odd-numbered vector elements from two n-dimensional source
739 /// vectors and write each result into consecutive elements of an
740 /// n-dimensional destination vector. Two shuffles are necessary to complete
741 /// the transpose, one for the even elements and another for the odd elements.
742 /// This description closely follows how the TRN1 and TRN2 AArch64
743 /// instructions operate.
744 ///
745 /// For example, a simple 2x2 matrix can be transposed with:
746 ///
747 /// ; Original matrix
748 /// m0 = < a, b >
749 /// m1 = < c, d >
750 ///
751 /// ; Transposed matrix
752 /// t0 = < a, c > = shufflevector m0, m1, < 0, 2 >
753 /// t1 = < b, d > = shufflevector m0, m1, < 1, 3 >
754 ///
755 /// For matrices having greater than n columns, the resulting nx2 transposed
756 /// matrix is stored in two result vectors such that one vector contains
757 /// interleaved elements from all the even-numbered rows and the other vector
758 /// contains interleaved elements from all the odd-numbered rows. For example,
759 /// a 2x4 matrix can be transposed with:
760 ///
761 /// ; Original matrix
762 /// m0 = < a, b, c, d >
763 /// m1 = < e, f, g, h >
764 ///
765 /// ; Transposed matrix
766 /// t0 = < a, e, c, g > = shufflevector m0, m1 < 0, 4, 2, 6 >
767 /// t1 = < b, f, d, h > = shufflevector m0, m1 < 1, 5, 3, 7 >
768 static bool isTransposeMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, int NumSrcElts) {
769 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isTransposeMask(Mask, NumSrcElts);
770 }
771 static bool isTransposeMask(const Constant *Mask, int NumSrcElts) {
772 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isTransposeMask(
773 cast<llvm::Constant>(Mask->Val), NumSrcElts);
774 }
775
776 /// Return true if this shuffle transposes the elements of its inputs without
777 /// changing the length of the vectors. This operation may also be known as a
778 /// merge or interleave. See the description for isTransposeMask() for the
779 /// exact specification.
780 /// Example: shufflevector <4 x n> A, <4 x n> B, <0,4,2,6>
781 bool isTranspose() const {
782 return cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Val)->isTranspose();
783 }
784
785 /// Return true if this shuffle mask is a splice mask, concatenating the two
786 /// inputs together and then extracts an original width vector starting from
787 /// the splice index.
788 /// Example: shufflevector <4 x n> A, <4 x n> B, <1,2,3,4>
789 /// This assumes that vector operands (of length \p NumSrcElts) are the same
790 /// length as the mask.
791 static bool isSpliceMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, int NumSrcElts, int &Index) {
792 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isSpliceMask(Mask, NumSrcElts, Index);
793 }

796 cast<llvm::Constant>(Mask->Val), NumSrcElts, Index);
797 }

802 /// Example: shufflevector <4 x n> A, <4 x n> B, <1,2,3,4>
803 bool isSplice(int &Index) const {
804 return cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Val)->isSplice(Index);

824 }

826 /// Return true if this shuffle mask is an insert subvector mask.

828 /// source operand into an in-place first source operand.
829 /// Both the sub vector width and the insertion index is returned.

831 int &NumSubElts, int &Index) {
832 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isInsertSubvectorMask(Mask, NumSrcElts,

847 /// Return true if this shuffle mask replicates each of the \p VF elements
848 /// in a vector \p ReplicationFactor times.
849 /// For example, the mask for \p ReplicationFactor=3 and \p VF=4 is:
850 /// <0,0,0,1,1,1,2,2,2,3,3,3>

868 /// Return true if this shuffle mask represents "clustered" mask of size VF,
869 /// i.e. each index between [0..VF) is used exactly once in each submask of
870 /// size VF.
871 /// For example, the mask for \p VF=4 is:
872 /// 0, 1, 2, 3, 3, 2, 0, 1 - "clustered", because each submask of size 4
873 /// (0,1,2,3 and 3,2,0,1) uses indices [0..VF) exactly one time.
874 /// 0, 1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 1, 0 - not "clustered", because
875 /// element 3 is used twice in the second submask
876 /// (3,3,1,0) and index 2 is not used at all.
877 static bool isOneUseSingleSourceMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, int VF) {
878 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isOneUseSingleSourceMask(Mask, VF);
879 }

882 /// mask.
883 bool isOneUseSingleSourceMask(int VF) const {
884 return cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Val)->isOneUseSingleSourceMask(VF);
885 }

887 /// Change values in a shuffle permute mask assuming the two vector operands
888 /// of length InVecNumElts have swapped position.

890 unsigned InVecNumElts) {
891 llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::commuteShuffleMask(Mask, InVecNumElts);
892 }

894 /// Return if this shuffle interleaves its two input vectors together.
895 bool isInterleave(unsigned Factor) const {
896 return cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Val)->isInterleave(Factor);
897 }
898
899 /// Return true if the mask interleaves one or more input vectors together.
900 ///
901 /// I.e. <0, LaneLen, ... , LaneLen*(Factor - 1), 1, LaneLen + 1, ...>
902 /// E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4):
903 /// <0, 4, 1, 5, 2, 6, 3, 7>
904 /// E.g. For a Factor of 3 (LaneLen=4):
905 /// <4, 0, 9, 5, 1, 10, 6, 2, 11, 7, 3, 12>
906 /// E.g. For a Factor of 4 (LaneLen=2):
907 /// <0, 2, 6, 4, 1, 3, 7, 5>
908 ///
909 /// NumInputElts is the total number of elements in the input vectors.
910 ///
911 /// StartIndexes are the first indexes of each vector being interleaved,
912 /// substituting any indexes that were undef
913 /// E.g. <4, -1, 2, 5, 1, 3> (Factor=3): StartIndexes=<4, 0, 2>
914 ///
915 /// Note that this does not check if the input vectors are consecutive:
916 /// It will return true for masks such as
917 /// <0, 4, 6, 1, 5, 7> (Factor=3, LaneLen=2)
918 static bool isInterleaveMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, unsigned Factor,
919 unsigned NumInputElts,
920 SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &StartIndexes) {
921 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isInterleaveMask(Mask, Factor, NumInputElts,
922 StartIndexes);
923 }
924 static bool isInterleaveMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, unsigned Factor,
925 unsigned NumInputElts) {
926 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isInterleaveMask(Mask, Factor,
927 NumInputElts);
928 }
929
930 /// Check if the mask is a DE-interleave mask of the given factor
931 /// \p Factor like:
932 /// <Index, Index+Factor, ..., Index+(NumElts-1)*Factor>
933 static bool isDeInterleaveMaskOfFactor(ArrayRef<int> Mask, unsigned Factor,
934 unsigned &Index) {
935 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isDeInterleaveMaskOfFactor(Mask, Factor,
936 Index);
937 }
938 static bool isDeInterleaveMaskOfFactor(ArrayRef<int> Mask, unsigned Factor) {
939 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isDeInterleaveMaskOfFactor(Mask, Factor);
940 }
941
942 /// Checks if the shuffle is a bit rotation of the first operand across
943 /// multiple subelements, e.g:
944 ///
945 /// shuffle <8 x i8> %a, <8 x i8> poison, <8 x i32> <1, 0, 3, 2, 5, 4, 7, 6>
946 ///
947 /// could be expressed as
948 ///
949 /// rotl <4 x i16> %a, 8
950 ///
951 /// If it can be expressed as a rotation, returns the number of subelements to
952 /// group by in NumSubElts and the number of bits to rotate left in RotateAmt.
953 static bool isBitRotateMask(ArrayRef<int> Mask, unsigned EltSizeInBits,
954 unsigned MinSubElts, unsigned MaxSubElts,
955 unsigned &NumSubElts, unsigned &RotateAmt) {
956 return llvm::ShuffleVectorInst::isBitRotateMask(
957 Mask, EltSizeInBits, MinSubElts, MaxSubElts, NumSubElts, RotateAmt);
958 }

1022class BranchInst : public SingleLLVMInstructionImpl<llvm::BranchInst> {
1023 /// Use Context::createBranchInst(). Don't call the constructor directly.
1024 BranchInst(llvm::BranchInst *BI, Context &Ctx)
1025 : SingleLLVMInstructionImpl(ClassID::Br, Opcode::Br, BI, Ctx) {}
1026 friend Context; // for BranchInst()
1027
1028public:
1029 static BranchInst *create(BasicBlock *IfTrue, Instruction *InsertBefore,
1030 Context &Ctx);
1031 static BranchInst *create(BasicBlock *IfTrue, BasicBlock *InsertAtEnd,
1032 Context &Ctx);
1033 static BranchInst *create(BasicBlock *IfTrue, BasicBlock *IfFalse,
1034 Value *Cond, Instruction *InsertBefore,
1035 Context &Ctx);
1036 static BranchInst *create(BasicBlock *IfTrue, BasicBlock *IfFalse,
1037 Value *Cond, BasicBlock *InsertAtEnd, Context &Ctx);
1038 /// For isa/dyn_cast.
1039 static bool classof(const Value *From);
1040 bool isUnconditional() const {
1041 return cast<llvm::BranchInst>(Val)->isUnconditional();
1042 }
1043 bool isConditional() const {
1044 return cast<llvm::BranchInst>(Val)->isConditional();
1045 }
1046 Value *getCondition() const;
1047 void setCondition(Value *V) { setOperand(0, V); }
1048 unsigned getNumSuccessors() const { return 1 + isConditional(); }
1049 BasicBlock *getSuccessor(unsigned SuccIdx) const;
1050 void setSuccessor(unsigned Idx, BasicBlock *NewSucc);
1051 void swapSuccessors() { swapOperandsInternal(1, 2); }

1053private:
1054 struct LLVMBBToSBBB {
1055 Context &Ctx;
1056 LLVMBBToSBBB(Context &Ctx) : Ctx(Ctx) {}
1057 BasicBlock *operator()(llvm::BasicBlock *BB) const;
1058 };
1059
1060 struct ConstLLVMBBToSBBB {
1061 Context &Ctx;
1062 ConstLLVMBBToSBBB(Context &Ctx) : Ctx(Ctx) {}
1063 const BasicBlock *operator()(const llvm::BasicBlock *BB) const;
1064 };
1065
1066public:
1067 using sb_succ_op_iterator =
1068 mapped_iterator<llvm::BranchInst::succ_op_iterator, LLVMBBToSBBB>;
1069 iterator_range<sb_succ_op_iterator> successors() {
1070 iterator_range<llvm::BranchInst::succ_op_iterator> LLVMRange =
1071 cast<llvm::BranchInst>(Val)->successors();
1072 LLVMBBToSBBB BBMap(Ctx);
1073 sb_succ_op_iterator MappedBegin = map_iterator(LLVMRange.begin(), BBMap);
1074 sb_succ_op_iterator MappedEnd = map_iterator(LLVMRange.end(), BBMap);
1075 return make_range(MappedBegin, MappedEnd);
1076 }
1077
1078 using const_sb_succ_op_iterator =
1079 mapped_iterator<llvm::BranchInst::const_succ_op_iterator,
1080 ConstLLVMBBToSBBB>;
1081 iterator_range<const_sb_succ_op_iterator> successors() const {
1082 iterator_range<llvm::BranchInst::const_succ_op_iterator> ConstLLVMRange =
1083 static_cast<const llvm::BranchInst *>(cast<llvm::BranchInst>(Val))
1084 ->successors();
1085 ConstLLVMBBToSBBB ConstBBMap(Ctx);
1086 const_sb_succ_op_iterator ConstMappedBegin =
1087 map_iterator(ConstLLVMRange.begin(), ConstBBMap);
1088 const_sb_succ_op_iterator ConstMappedEnd =
1089 map_iterator(ConstLLVMRange.end(), ConstBBMap);
1090 return make_range(ConstMappedBegin, ConstMappedEnd);
1091 }

1311class CallBase : public SingleLLVMInstructionImpl<llvm::CallBase> {

1313 : SingleLLVMInstructionImpl(ID, Opc, I, Ctx) {}

1317
1318public:
1319 static bool classof(const Value *From) {
1320 auto Opc = From->getSubclassID();

1322 Opc == Instruction::ClassID::Invoke ||
1323 Opc == Instruction::ClassID::CallBr;
1324 }
1325
1326 FunctionType *getFunctionType() const;
1327
1328 op_iterator data_operands_begin() { return op_begin(); }
1329 const_op_iterator data_operands_begin() const {
1330 return const_cast<CallBase *>(this)->data_operands_begin();
1331 }
1332 op_iterator data_operands_end() {
1333 auto *LLVMCB = cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val);
1334 auto Dist = LLVMCB->data_operands_end() - LLVMCB->data_operands_begin();
1335 return op_begin() + Dist;
1336 }
1337 const_op_iterator data_operands_end() const {
1338 auto *LLVMCB = cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val);
1339 auto Dist = LLVMCB->data_operands_end() - LLVMCB->data_operands_begin();
1340 return op_begin() + Dist;
1341 }
1342 iterator_range<op_iterator> data_ops() {
1343 return make_range(data_operands_begin(), data_operands_end());
1344 }
1345 iterator_range<const_op_iterator> data_ops() const {
1346 return make_range(data_operands_begin(), data_operands_end());
1347 }
1348 bool data_operands_empty() const {
1349 return data_operands_end() == data_operands_begin();
1350 }
1351 unsigned data_operands_size() const {
1352 return std::distance(data_operands_begin(), data_operands_end());
1353 }
1354 bool isDataOperand(Use U) const {
1355 assert(this == U.getUser() &&
1356 "Only valid to query with a use of this instruction!");
1357 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isDataOperand(U.LLVMUse);
1358 }
1359 unsigned getDataOperandNo(Use U) const {
1360 assert(isDataOperand(U) && "Data operand # out of range!");
1361 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->getDataOperandNo(U.LLVMUse);
1362 }
1363
1364 /// Return the total number operands (not operand bundles) used by
1365 /// every operand bundle in this OperandBundleUser.
1366 unsigned getNumTotalBundleOperands() const {
1367 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->getNumTotalBundleOperands();
1368 }
1369
1370 op_iterator arg_begin() { return op_begin(); }
1371 const_op_iterator arg_begin() const { return op_begin(); }
1372 op_iterator arg_end() {
1373 return data_operands_end() - getNumTotalBundleOperands();
1374 }
1375 const_op_iterator arg_end() const {
1376 return const_cast<CallBase *>(this)->arg_end();
1377 }
1378 iterator_range<op_iterator> args() {
1379 return make_range(arg_begin(), arg_end());
1380 }
1381 iterator_range<const_op_iterator> args() const {
1382 return make_range(arg_begin(), arg_end());
1383 }
1384 bool arg_empty() const { return arg_end() == arg_begin(); }
1385 unsigned arg_size() const { return arg_end() - arg_begin(); }
1386
1387 Value *getArgOperand(unsigned OpIdx) const {
1388 assert(OpIdx < arg_size() && "Out of bounds!");
1389 return getOperand(OpIdx);
1390 }
1391 void setArgOperand(unsigned OpIdx, Value *NewOp) {
1392 assert(OpIdx < arg_size() && "Out of bounds!");
1393 setOperand(OpIdx, NewOp);
1394 }
1395
1396 Use getArgOperandUse(unsigned Idx) const {
1397 assert(Idx < arg_size() && "Out of bounds!");
1398 return getOperandUse(Idx);
1399 }
1400 Use getArgOperandUse(unsigned Idx) {
1401 assert(Idx < arg_size() && "Out of bounds!");
1402 return getOperandUse(Idx);
1403 }
1404
1405 bool isArgOperand(Use U) const {
1406 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isArgOperand(U.LLVMUse);
1407 }
1408 unsigned getArgOperandNo(Use U) const {
1409 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->getArgOperandNo(U.LLVMUse);
1410 }

1412
1413 Value *getCalledOperand() const;
1414 Use getCalledOperandUse() const;
1415
1416 Function *getCalledFunction() const;
1417 bool isIndirectCall() const {
1418 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isIndirectCall();
1419 }
1420 bool isCallee(Use U) const {
1421 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isCallee(U.LLVMUse);
1422 }
1423 Function *getCaller();
1424 const Function *getCaller() const {
1425 return const_cast<CallBase *>(this)->getCaller();
1426 }
1427 bool isMustTailCall() const {
1428 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isMustTailCall();
1429 }
1430 bool isTailCall() const { return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->isTailCall(); }
1431 Intrinsic::ID getIntrinsicID() const {
1432 return cast<llvm::CallBase>(Val)->getIntrinsicID();
1433 }
1434 void setCalledOperand(Value *V) { getCalledOperandUse().set(V); }

1804 CSI, Ctx) {}
1805
1806 static CatchSwitchInst *create(Value *ParentPad, BasicBlock *UnwindBB,
1807 unsigned NumHandlers, BBIterator WhereIt,
1808 BasicBlock *WhereBB, Context &Ctx,
1809 const Twine &Name = "");
1810
1811 Value *getParentPad() const;

1813
1814 bool hasUnwindDest() const {
1815 return cast<llvm::CatchSwitchInst>(Val)->hasUnwindDest();
1816 }
1817 bool unwindsToCaller() const {
1818 return cast<llvm::CatchSwitchInst>(Val)->unwindsToCaller();
1819 }
1820 BasicBlock *getUnwindDest() const;

1822
1823 unsigned getNumHandlers() const {
1824 return cast<llvm::CatchSwitchInst>(Val)->getNumHandlers();
1825 }
1826
1827private:
1828 static BasicBlock *handler_helper(Value *V) { return cast<BasicBlock>(V); }
1829 static const BasicBlock *handler_helper(const Value *V) {
1830 return cast<BasicBlock>(V);
1831 }
1832
1833public:
1834 using DerefFnTy = BasicBlock *(*)(Value *);
1835 using handler_iterator = mapped_iterator<op_iterator, DerefFnTy>;
1836 using handler_range = iterator_range<handler_iterator>;
1837 using ConstDerefFnTy = const BasicBlock *(*)(const Value *);
1838 using const_handler_iterator =
1839 mapped_iterator<const_op_iterator, ConstDerefFnTy>;
1840 using const_handler_range = iterator_range<const_handler_iterator>;
1841
1842 handler_iterator handler_begin() {
1843 op_iterator It = op_begin() + 1;
1844 if (hasUnwindDest())
1845 ++It;
1846 return handler_iterator(It, DerefFnTy(handler_helper));
1847 }
1848 const_handler_iterator handler_begin() const {
1849 const_op_iterator It = op_begin() + 1;
1850 if (hasUnwindDest())
1851 ++It;
1852 return const_handler_iterator(It, ConstDerefFnTy(handler_helper));
1853 }
1854 handler_iterator handler_end() {
1855 return handler_iterator(op_end(), DerefFnTy(handler_helper));
1856 }
1857 const_handler_iterator handler_end() const {
1858 return const_handler_iterator(op_end(), ConstDerefFnTy(handler_helper));
1859 }
1860 handler_range handlers() {
1861 return make_range(handler_begin(), handler_end());
1862 }
1863 const_handler_range handlers() const {
1864 return make_range(handler_begin(), handler_end());
1865 }
1866
1867 void addHandler(BasicBlock *Dest);
1868
1869 // TODO: removeHandler() cannot be reverted because there is no equivalent
1870 // addHandler() with a handler_iterator to specify the position. So we can't
1871 // implement it for now.
1872
1873 unsigned getNumSuccessors() const { return getNumOperands() - 1; }
1874 BasicBlock *getSuccessor(unsigned Idx) const {
1875 assert(Idx < getNumSuccessors() &&
1876 "Successor # out of range for catchswitch!");
1877 return cast<BasicBlock>(getOperand(Idx + 1));
1878 }
1879 void setSuccessor(unsigned Idx, BasicBlock *NewSucc) {
1880 assert(Idx < getNumSuccessors() &&
1881 "Successor # out of range for catchswitch!");
1882 setOperand(Idx + 1, NewSucc);
1883 }
1884
1885 static bool classof(const Value *From) {
1886 return From->getSubclassID() == ClassID::CatchSwitch;
1887 }
